---
import Site from '../layouts/Site.astro';
import PageHeader from '../components/PageHeader.astro';
import { SITE } from '../lib/config';
---

<Site title="About" description="About this site and its author.">
  <PageHeader title="About" />

  <div class="px-5 pb-20">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto prose dark:prose-invert prose-stone">

      <p>
        I'm not trying to be consistent. I'm trying to be honest.
      </p>

      <p>
        This website is a record of how I think — not a polished version of it.
        The essays, logs, ideas, and quotes here are snapshots. Some will age well.
        Some won't. That's the point.
      </p>

      <p>
        Lately I've been obsessed with how ideas form — how a loose thought becomes
        a conviction, how a conviction gets dismantled by a single good sentence.
        Articulation fascinates me not as a performance skill but as a thinking tool.
        If I can't write it clearly, I probably don't understand it yet.
      </p>

      <p>
        I document because I want to be a reliable narrator of my own life. Not for
        anyone else — for the version of me ten years from now who will read this and
        either cringe or nod. Both are useful.
      </p>

      <p>
        The things that hold my attention right now: curating ideas worth keeping,
        writing that earns its length, and the gap between what people say they
        believe and how they actually live.
      </p>

      <h2>What's here</h2>

      <p>
        <a href="/writings">Writings</a> are longer essays — attempts to think clearly
        about things that are hard to think clearly about. <a href="/logs">Logs</a> are
        shorter: fragments, observations, and updates that don't warrant a full essay
        but feel worth preserving. <a href="/ideas">Ideas</a> are even looser — single
        thoughts, sometimes threaded together when one pulls on another.
        <a href="/quotes">Quotes</a> are lines I keep returning to, collected from
        books and conversations. <a href="/links">Links</a> are things worth reading
        elsewhere. The <a href="/bookshelf">bookshelf</a> tracks what I've read and
        what left a mark. The <a href="/problems">problems</a> page is a running list
        of things I'm thinking through — defined clearly, tracked honestly, marked
        solved when they are. The <a href="/now">now page</a> is a snapshot of what
        I'm currently doing.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>

      <p>
        Email is the best way to reach me:
        <a href={`mailto:${SITE.email}`}>{SITE.email}</a>
      </p>

      <p>
        I read every message. I reply slowly but genuinely.
      </p>

    </div>
  </div>
</Site>